page.title: 05BIRDS AND INSECTS,AYLESFORD
page.content: At St Peters Scool 81 people were given a form asking how many birds they had seen,and if they feed the birds.60 people did feed the birds.Almost everyone saw Robins,Sparrows and Blackbirds.There were some unusual birds too:Little and Barn Owl,Oyster Catcher,Snipe and Heron.71 different birds had been seen of which 50 were common birds.There were 3 winter migrants.22 species of butterfly have been identified in the area.Small Tortoiseshell and Large and Small White are very common.Rarer varieties include the Painted lady and Chalkhill Blue.
